        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 10:37PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 1037 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Feterita, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern
Morton, southeastern Stanton and northwestern Stevens Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
southwestern Kansas.</instruction>
